le="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_down" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 6 12 18 22 6" /></svg></a></div><a class="avatar_container" href="https://itch.io/profile/jedb"><div class="post_avatar" style="background-image: url(https://img.itch.zone/aW1nLzc0NDAxOTguanBn/25x25%23/MnYtuW.jpg)"></div></a><div class="post_header"><span class="post_author"><a href="https://itch.io/profile/jedb">Julien Bartholini</a></span><span class="post_date" title="2023-02-24 19:31:51"><a href="https://itch.io/post/7388537">125 days ago</a></span><span class="vote_counts"></span></div><div class="post_content"><div class="post_body user_formatted" dir="auto"><p></p><p>yes I understand your idea, thank you for answering :).</p>  <p>At the time, I very quickly eliminated the idea of automatic dialogues because it risked harming reading comfort for people who might have encountered difficulties such as lack of practice in reading, sight problems, dyslexia, etc... It was also more practical to give foreign players time to translate the text.</p>  <p>Suddenly manual reading had so many advantages that I did not even consider another way to do it as a bonus option.</p></div><div class="post_footer"><a data-register_action="community_reply" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" class="post_action reply_btn">Reply</a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div id="post-7377166" data-post="{&quot;id&quot;:7377166,&quot;user_id&quot;:6385701}" class="community_post has_replies has_vote_column"><div class="post_grid"><div class="post_votes"><a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" title="Vote up" class="vote_up_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_up" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 18 12 6 22 18" /></svg></a> <a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" title="Vote down" class="vote_down_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_down" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 6 12 18 22 6" /></svg></a></div><a class="avatar_container" href="https://itch.io/profile/omnixo"><div class="post_avatar" style="background-image: url(https://img.itch.zone/aW1nLzEwMjY4OTE3LnBuZw==/25x25%23/KLUtJo.png)"></div></a><div class="post_header"><span class="post_author"><a href="https://itch.io/profile/omnixo">omnixo</a></span><span class="post_date" title="2023-02-22 20:27:39"><a href="https://itch.io/post/7377166">127 days ago</a></span><span class="vote_counts"></span></div><div class="post_content"><div class="post_body user_formatted" dir="auto"><p>I&#x27;ve got to say I really enjoyed it! It&#x27;s got a great atmosphere. The eerie vibes are well done and ever-present!&nbsp;<br><br>It does a better job at being creepy than 90% of Hollywood movies! Also, the ending was nice too! The pacing and the final shot, conveys so much without beating you in the head with exposition!<br><br><br>Well done! If you ever consider making something longer you&#x27;ve got a buyer right here!</p></div><div class="post_footer"><a data-register_action="community_reply" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" class="post_action reply_btn">Reply</a></div></div></div></div><div class="community_post_replies top_level_replies"><div id="post-7384349" data-post="{&quot;id&quot;:7384349,&quot;user_id&quot;:5092358}" class="community_post has_replies is_reply has_vote_column"><div class="post_grid"><div class="post_votes"><a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" title="Vote up" class="vote_up_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_up" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 18 12 6 22 18" /></svg></a> <a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" title="Vote down" class="vote_down_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_down" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 6 12 18 22 6" /></svg></a></div><a class="avatar_container" href="https://itch.io/profile/jedb"><div class="post_avatar" style="background-image: url(https://img.itch.zone/aW1nLzc0NDAxOTguanBn/25x25%23/MnYtuW.jpg)"></div></a><div class="post_header"><span class="post_author"><a href="https://itch.io/profile/jedb">Julien Bartholini</a></span><span class="post_date" title="2023-02-24 00:24:48"><a href="https://itch.io/post/7384349">126 days ago</a></span><span class="vote_counts"><span class="upvotes">(+1)</span></span></div><div class="post_content"><div class="post_body user_formatted" dir="auto"><p></p><p>Thank you so much, omnixo :-)<br><br>It&#x27;s my very first game and I wanted to compensate for its linearity with staged elements. I intend to create another game. Probably still on the theme of the &quot;haunted house&quot;. I&#x27;m still thinking.</p>  <p>Thanks again ! I really appreciated your comment, omnixo.<br> Greetings from France.<br></p></div><div class="post_footer"><a data-register_action="community_reply" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" class="post_action reply_btn">Reply</a></div></div></div></div><div class="community_post_replies"><div id="post-7417790" data-post="{&quot;id&quot;:7417790,&quot;user_id&quot;:6385701}" class="community_post has_replies is_reply has_vote_column"><div class="post_grid"><div class="post_votes"><a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" title="Vote up" class="vote_up_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_up" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 18 12 6 22 18" /></svg></a> <a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" title="Vote down" class="vote_down_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_down" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 6 12 18 22 6" /></svg></a></div><a class="avatar_container" href="https://itch.io/profile/omnixo"><div class="post_avatar" style="background-image: url(https://img.itch.zone/aW1nLzEwMjY4OTE3LnBuZw==/25x25%23/KLUtJo.png)"></div></a><div class="post_header"><span class="post_author"><a href="https://itch.io/profile/omnixo">omnixo</a></span><span class="post_date" title="2023-03-01 14:38:30"><a href="https://itch.io/post/7417790">120 days ago</a></span><span class="vote_counts"><span class="upvotes">(+1)</span></span></div><div class="post_content"><div class="post_body user_formatted" dir="auto"><p>Please do not keep us in the dark if once the game goes into testing phase and of course, when it gets eventually released. Would love to support an independent dev!</p></div><div class="post_footer"><a data-register_action="community_reply" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" class="post_action reply_btn">Reply</a></div></div></div></div><div class="community_post_replies"><div id="post-7430222" data-post="{&quot;id&quot;:7430222,&quot;user_id&quot;:5092358}" class="community_post is_reply has_vote_column"><div class="post_grid"><div class="post_votes"><a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" title="Vote up" class="vote_up_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_up" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 18 12 6 22 18" /></svg></a> <a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" title="Vote down" class="vote_down_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_down" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 6 12 18 22 6" /></svg></a></div><a class="avatar_container" href="https://itch.io/profile/jedb"><div class="post_avatar" style="background-image: url(https://img.itch.zone/aW1nLzc0NDAxOTguanBn/25x25%23/MnYtuW.jpg)"></div></a><div class="post_header"><span class="post_author"><a href="https://itch.io/profile/jedb">Julien Bartholini</a></span><span class="post_date" title="2023-03-03 19:32:37"><a href="https://itch.io/post/7430222">118 days ago</a></span><span class="vote_counts"></span></div><div class="post_content"><div class="post_body user_formatted" dir="auto"><p>This is the kind of message that feels good. Thank you so much omnixo :-)<br></p></div><div class="post_footer"><a data-register_action="community_reply" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" class="post_action reply_btn">Reply</a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div id="post-7368656" data-post="{&quot;id&quot;:7368656,&quot;user_id&quot;:6505077}" class="community_post has_replies has_vote_column"><div class="post_grid"><div class="post_votes"><a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" title="Vote up" class="vote_up_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_up" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 18 12 6 22 18" /></svg></a> <a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" title="Vote down" class="vote_down_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_down" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 6 12 18 22 6" /></svg></a></div><a class="avatar_container" href="https://itch.io/profile/watormalon"><div class="post_avatar" style="background-image: url(/static/images/frog-red.png)"></div></a><div class="post_header"><span class="post_author"><a href="https://itch.io/profile/watormalon">Watormalon</a></span><span class="post_date" title="2023-02-21 16:14:37"><a href="https://itch.io/post/7368656">128 days ago</a></span><span class="vote_counts"></span></div><div class="post_content"><div class="post_body user_formatted" dir="auto"><p>This game is simply.... AMAZING. I beat it soo many times and was still frightened, goofed, and got great moments watching my friends play it</p></div><div class="post_footer"><a data-register_action="community_reply" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" class="post_action reply_btn">Reply</a></div></div></div></div><div class="community_post_replies top_level_replies"><div id="post-7371112" data-post="{&quot;id&quot;:7371112,&quot;user_id&quot;:5092358}" class="community_post is_reply has_vote_column"><div class="post_grid"><div class="post_votes"><a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" title="Vote up" class="vote_up_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_up" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 18 12 6 22 18" /></svg></a> <a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" title="Vote down" class="vote_down_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_down" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 6 12 18 22 6" /></svg></a></div><a class="avatar_container" href="https://itch.io/profile/jedb"><div class="post_avatar" style="background-image: url(https://img.itch.zone/aW1nLzc0NDAxOTguanBn/25x25%23/MnYtuW.jpg)"></div></a><div class="post_header"><span class="post_author"><a href="https://itch.io/profile/jedb">Julien Bartholini</a></span><span class="post_date" title="2023-02-21 22:04:42"><a href="https://itch.io/post/7371112">128 days ago</a></span><span class="vote_counts"></span></div><div class="post_content"><div class="post_body user_formatted" dir="auto"><p></p><p>Thank you very much Watormalon :-)<br> It makes me very happy to know that my work has been able to bring some good moments to other people. I imagine the sadistic moment when you wait to see the reaction of your friends ^^.<br>Thanks again and greetings from France.<br></p></div><div class="post_footer"><a data-register_action="community_reply" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" class="post_action reply_btn">Reply</a></div></div></div></div></div><div id="post-7337529" data-post="{&quot;id&quot;:7337529,&quot;user_id&quot;:4161503}" class="community_post has_replies has_vote_column"><div class="post_grid"><div class="post_votes"><a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" title="Vote up" class="vote_up_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_up" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 18 12 6 22 18" /></svg></a> <a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" title="Vote down" class="vote_down_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_down" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 6 12 18 22 6" /></svg></a></div><a class="avatar_container" href="https://itch.io/profile/woodyrun"><div class="post_avatar" style="background-image: url(https://img.itch.zone/aW1nLzY5NDk5NjkucG5n/25x25%23/88lmRC.png)"></div></a><div class="post_header"><span class="post_author"><a href="https://itch.io/profile/woodyrun">WoodyRun</a></span><span class="post_date" title="2023-02-17 22:16:35"><a href="https://itch.io/post/7337529">132 days ago</a></span> <span class="edit_message">(1 edit)</span> <span class="vote_counts"><span class="upvotes">(+1)</span></span></div><div class="post_content"><div class="post_body user_formatted" dir="auto"><p></p>  <div><button itchio aria-label="Click to activate YouTube embed" type="button" class="embed_preload youtube_preload" data-embed_code="&lt;iframe width=&quot;500&quot; height=&quot;281&quot; src=&quot;//www.youtube.com/embed/TRuenRsgMsc&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allowfullscreen=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;" style="width: 250px; height: 140px; background: url(https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TRuenRsgMsc/hqdefault.jpg) 50% 50% no-repeat; background-size: cover"></button></div>  <p>Around a year ago, I played this game and I loved it. It scared me so bad I unplugged my microphone accidentally and lost the rest of the audio for the recording! I wanted to wait until I forgot about the game to play it again because I really wanted to make a video about this game, it was that good.&nbsp;<br></p><p></p>  <p>I finally got around to replaying it and thankfully I didn&#x27;t lose audio this time but I did get just as scared, if not more, than last time. You probably don&#x27;t need me to tell you this but this is an amazing horror game. I consider this to be 10/10 horror. I think other indie horror games should aspire to be as good as this one. The style, the atmosphere, the monsters, the scares, the story, etc. everything is done so well.&nbsp;</p>  <p>You&#x27;ve made a masterpiece.&nbsp;</p><p>Thank you for making it!</p></div><div class="post_footer"><a data-register_action="community_reply" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" class="post_action reply_btn">Reply</a></div></div></div></div><div class="community_post_replies top_level_replies"><div id="post-7338600" data-post="{&quot;id&quot;:7338600,&quot;user_id&quot;:5092358}" class="community_post is_reply has_vote_column"><div class="post_grid"><div class="post_votes"><a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" title="Vote up" class="vote_up_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_up" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 18 12 6 22 18" /></svg></a> <a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjedb.itch.io%2Finvitationem&amp;intent=community" title="Vote down" class="vote_down_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_down" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 6 12 18 22 6" /></svg></a></div><a class="avatar_container" href="https://itch.io/profile/jedb"><div class="post_avatar" style="background-image: url(https://img.itch.zone/aW1nLzc0NDAxOTguanBn/25x25%23/MnYtuW.jpg)"></div></a><div class="post_header"><span class="post_author"><a href="https://itch.io/profile/jedb">Julien Bartholini</a></span><span class="post_date" title="2023-02-18 02:53:48"><a href="https://itch.io/post/7338600">132 days ago</a></span><span class="vote_counts"><span class="upvotes">(+1)</span></span></div><div class="post_content"><div class="post_body user_formatted" dir="auto"><p></p><p>(I post you here the comment that I put under your YouTube video. Thank you again for all your compliments. They made me very happy ! :3)<br></p><p>It&